title: Fiberglass laminators and fabricators
def: Laminate layers of fiberglass on molds to form boat decks and hulls, bodies for golf carts, automobiles, or other products.

title: Timing device assemblers and adjusters
def: Perform precision assembling or adjusting, within narrow tolerances, of timing devices such as digital clocks or timing devices with electrical or electronic components. Watchmakers are included in “Watch and Clock Repairers” (49-9064).

title: Miscellaneous assemblers and fabricators
def: No job definition found.

title: Food processing workers
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Bakers
def: Mix and bake ingredients to produce breads, rolls, cookies, cakes, pies, pastries, or other baked goods. Pastry chefs in restaurants and hotels are included with “Chefs and Head Cooks” (35-1011).

title: Butchers and other meat, poultry, etc
soc_title: Butchers and Other Meat, Poultry, and Fish Processing Workers
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Butchers and meat cutters
def: Cut, trim, or prepare consumer-sized portions of meat for use or sale in retail establishments.

title: Meat, poultry, etc
soc_title: Meat, Poultry, and Fish Cutters and Trimmers
def: Use hands or hand tools to perform routine cutting and trimming of meat, poultry, and seafood.

title: Slaughterers and meat packers
def: Perform nonroutine or precision functions involving the preparation of large portions of meat. Work may include specialized slaughtering tasks, cutting standard or premium cuts of meat for marketing, making sausage, or wrapping meats. Work typically occurs in slaughtering, meat packing, or wholesale establishments. Excludes “Meat, Poultry, and Fish Cutters and Trimmers” (51-3022) who perform routine meat cutting.

title: Miscellaneous food processing workers
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Food and tobacco roasting, baking, etc
soc_title: Food and Tobacco Roasting, Baking, and Drying Machine Operators and Tenders
def: Operate or tend food or tobacco roasting, baking, or drying equipment, including hearth ovens, kiln driers, roasters, char kilns, and vacuum drying equipment.

title: Food batchmakers
def: Set up and operate equipment that mixes or blends ingredients used in the manufacturing of food products. Includes candy makers and cheese makers.

title: Food cooking machine operators and tenders
soc_title: Food Cooking Machine Operators and Tenders
def: Operate or tend cooking equipment, such as steam cooking vats, deep fry cookers, pressure cookers, kettles, and boilers, to prepare food products. Excludes “Food and Tobacco Roasting, Baking, and Drying Machine Operators and Tenders” (51-3091).

title: Food processing workers, all other
def: All food processing workers not listed separately

title: Metal workers and plastic workers
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Forming machine setters, operators, etc
soc_title: Forming Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Extruding and drawing machine setters, operators, etc
soc_title: Extruding and Drawing Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
def: Set up, operate, or tend machines to extrude or draw thermoplastic or metal materials into tubes, rods, hoses, wire, bars, or structural shapes.

title: Forging machine setters, operators, etc
soc_title: Forging Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
def: Set up, operate, or tend forging machines to taper, shape, or form metal or plastic parts.

title: Rolling machine setters, operators, etc
soc_title: Rolling Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
def: Set up, operate, or tend machines to roll steel or plastic forming bends, beads, knurls, rolls, or plate, or to flatten, temper, or reduce gauge of material.

title: Machine tool cutting setters, operators, etc
soc_title: Machine Tool Cutting Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Cutting, punching, etc
soc_title: Cutting, Punching, and Press Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
def: Set up, operate, or tend machines to saw, cut, shear, slit, punch, crimp, notch, bend, or straighten metal or plastic material.

title: Drilling and boring machine tool setters, operators, etc
soc_title: Drilling and Boring Machine Tool Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
def: Set up, operate, or tend drilling machines to drill, bore, ream, mill, or countersink metal or plastic work pieces.

title: Grinding, lapping, etc
soc_title: Grinding, Lapping, Polishing, and Buffing Machine Tool Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
def: Set up, operate, or tend grinding and related tools that remove excess material or burrs from surfaces, sharpen edges or corners, or buff, hone, or polish metal or plastic work pieces.

title: Lathe and turning machine tool setters, operators, etc
soc_title: Lathe and Turning Machine Tool Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
def: Set up, operate, or tend lathe and turning machines to turn, bore, thread, form, or face metal or plastic materials, such as wire, rod, or bar stock.

title: Milling and planing machine setters, operators, etc
soc_title: Milling and Planing Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
def: Set up, operate, or tend milling or planing machines to mill, plane, shape, groove, or profile metal or plastic work pieces.

title: Machinists
def: Set up and operate a variety of machine tools to produce precision parts and instruments out of metal. Includes precision instrument makers who fabricate, modify, or repair mechanical instruments. May also fabricate and modify parts to make or repair machine tools or maintain industrial machines, applying knowledge of mechanics, mathematics, metal properties, layout, and machining procedures. Machinists who primarily program or operate computer numerically controlled (CNC) equipment are classified in “Computer Numerically Controlled Tool Operators and Programmers” (51-9160).

title: Metal furnace operators, tenders, etc
soc_title: Metal Furnace Operators, Tenders, Pourers, and Casters
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Metal-refining furnace operators and tenders
def: Operate or tend furnaces, such as gas, oil, coal, electric-arc or electric induction, open-hearth, or oxygen furnaces, to melt and refine metal before casting or to produce specified types of steel. Excludes “Heat Treating Equipment Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic” (51-4191).

title: Pourers and casters, metal
def: Operate hand-controlled mechanisms to pour and regulate the flow of molten metal into molds to produce castings or ingots.

title: Model makers and patternmakers, metal and plastic
soc_title: Model Makers and Patternmakers, Metal and Plastic
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Model makers, metal and plastic
def: Set up and operate machines, such as lathes, milling and engraving machines, and jig borers to make working models of metal or plastic objects. Includes template makers.

title: Patternmakers, metal and plastic
def: Lay out, machine, fit, and assemble castings and parts to metal or plastic foundry patterns, core boxes, or match plates.

title: Molders and molding machine setters, operators, etc
soc_title: Molders and Molding Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Foundry mold and coremakers
def: Make or form wax or sand cores or molds used in the production of metal castings in foundries. Excludes “Molding, Coremaking, and Casting Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic” (51-4072) and “Molders, Shapers, and Casters, Except Metal and Plastic” (51-9195).

title: Molding, coremaking, etc
soc_title: Molding, Coremaking, and Casting Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
def: Set up, operate, or tend metal or plastic molding, casting, or coremaking machines to mold or cast metal or thermoplastic parts or products.

title: Multiple machine tool setters, operators, etc
soc_title: Multiple Machine Tool Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
def: Set up, operate, or tend more than one type of cutting or forming machine tool or robot.

title: Tool and die makers
def: Analyze specifications, lay out metal stock, set up and operate machine tools, and fit and assemble parts to make and repair dies, cutting tools, jigs, fixtures, gauges, and machinists’ hand tools.

title: Welding, soldering, etc
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Welders, cutters, etc
def: Use hand-welding, flame-cutting, hand-soldering, or brazing equipment to weld or join metal components or to fill holes, indentations, or seams of fabricated metal products.

title: Welding, soldering, etc
soc_title: Welding, Soldering, and Brazing Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
def: Set up, operate, or tend welding, soldering, or brazing machines or robots that weld, braze, solder, or heat treat metal products, components, or assemblies. Includes workers who operate laser cutters or laser-beam machines.

title: Miscellaneous metal workers and plastic workers
soc_title: Miscellaneous Metal Workers and Plastic Workers
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Heat treating equipment setters, operators, etc
soc_title: Heat Treating Equipment Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
def: Set up, operate, or tend heating equipment, such as heat-treating furnaces, flame-hardening machines, induction machines, soaking pits, or vacuum equipment to temper, harden, anneal, or heat treat metal or plastic objects.

title: Layout workers, metal and plastic
def: Lay out reference points and dimensions on metal or plastic stock or workpieces, such as sheets, plates, tubes, structural shapes, castings, or machine parts, for further processing. Includes shipfitters.

title: Plating machine setters, operators, etc
soc_title: Plating Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
def: Set up, operate, or tend plating machines to coat metal or plastic products with chromium, zinc, copper, cadmium, nickel, or other metal to protect or decorate surfaces. Typically, the product being coated is immersed in molten metal or an electrolytic solution. Excludes “Coating, Painting, and Spraying Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders” (51-9124).

title: Tool grinders, filers, etc
def: Perform precision smoothing, sharpening, polishing, or grinding of metal objects.

title: Metal workers and plastic workers, all other
soc_title: Metal Workers and Plastic Workers, All Other
def: All metal workers and plastic workers not listed separately.

title: Printing workers
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Prepress technicians and workers
def: Format and proof text and images submitted by designers and clients into finished pages that can be printed. Includes digital and photo typesetting. May produce printing plates.

title: Printing press operators
def: Set up and operate digital, letterpress, lithographic, flexographic, gravure, or other printing machines. Includes short-run offset printing presses.

title: Print binding and finishing workers
def: Bind books and other publications or finish printed products by hand or machine. May set up binding and finishing machines.

title: Textile, apparel, etc
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Laundry and dry-cleaning workers
def: Operate or tend washing or dry-cleaning machines to wash or dry-clean industrial or household articles, such as cloth garments, suede, leather, furs, blankets, draperies, linens, rugs, and carpets. Includes spotters and dyers of these articles.

title: Pressers, textile, etc
soc_title: Pressers, Textile, Garment, and Related Materials
def: Press or shape articles by hand or machine.

title: Sewing machine operators
def: Operate or tend sewing machines to join, reinforce, decorate, or perform related sewing operations in the manufacture of garment or nongarment products.

title: Shoe and leather workers
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Shoe and leather workers and repairers
soc_title: Shoe and Leather Workers and Repairers
def: Construct, decorate, or repair leather and leather-like products, such as luggage, shoes, and saddles. May use hand tools.

title: Shoe machine operators and tenders
def: Operate or tend a variety of machines to join, decorate, reinforce, or finish shoes and shoe parts.

title: Tailors, dressmakers, etc
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Sewers, hand
def: Sew, join, reinforce, or finish, usually with needle and thread, a variety of manufactured items. Includes weavers and stitchers.

title: Tailors, dressmakers, etc
def: Design, make, alter, repair, or fit garments.

title: Textile machine setters, operators, etc
soc_title: Textile Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Textile bleaching and dyeing machine operators and tenders
soc_title: Textile Bleaching and Dyeing Machine Operators and Tenders
def: Operate or tend machines to bleach, shrink, wash, dye, or finish textiles or synthetic or glass fibers.

title: Textile cutting machine setters, operators, etc
soc_title: Textile Cutting Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
def: Set up, operate, or tend machines that cut textiles.

title: Textile knitting and weaving machine setters, operators, etc
soc_title: Textile Knitting and Weaving Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
def: Set up, operate, or tend machines that knit, loop, weave, or draw in textiles. Excludes “Sewing Machine Operators” (51-6031).

title: Textile winding, twisting, etc
soc_title: Textile Winding, Twisting, and Drawing Out Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
def: Set up, operate, or tend machines that wind or twist textiles; or draw out and combine sliver, such as wool, hemp, or synthetic fibers. Includes slubber machine and drawing frame operators.

title: Miscellaneous textile, apparel, etc
soc_title: Miscellaneous Textile, Apparel, and Furnishings Workers
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Extruding and forming machine setters, operators, etc
soc_title: Extruding and Forming Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Synthetic and Glass Fibers
def: Set up, operate, or tend machines that extrude and form continuous filaments from synthetic materials, such as liquid polymer, rayon, and fiberglass.

title: Fabric and apparel patternmakers
def: Draw and construct sets of precision master fabric patterns or layouts. May also mark and cut fabrics and apparel.

title: Upholsterers
def: Make, repair, or replace upholstery for household furniture or transportation vehicles.

title: Textile, apparel, etc
soc_title: Textile, Apparel, and Furnishings Workers, All Other
def: All textile, apparel, and furnishings workers not listed separately.

title: Woodworkers
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Cabinetmakers and bench carpenters
def: Cut, shape, and assemble wooden articles or set up and operate a variety of woodworking machines, such as power saws, jointers, and mortisers to surface, cut, or shape lumber or to fabricate parts for wood products. Excludes “Woodworking Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders” (51-7040).

title: Furniture finishers
def: Shape, finish, and refinish damaged, worn, or used furniture or new high-grade furniture to specified color or finish.

title: Model makers and patternmakers, wood
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Model makers, wood
def: Construct full-size and scale wooden precision models of products. Includes wood jig builders and loft workers.

title: Patternmakers, wood
def: Plan, lay out, and construct wooden unit or sectional patterns used in forming sand molds for castings.

title: Woodworking machine setters, operators, etc
soc_title: Woodworking Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Sawing machine setters, operators, etc
soc_title: Sawing Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Wood
def: Set up, operate, or tend wood sawing machines. May operate computer numerically controlled (CNC) equipment. Includes lead sawyers. Workers who primarily program or operate CNC equipment are classified in “Computer Numerically Controlled Tool Operators and Programmers” (51-9160).

title: Woodworking machine setters, operators, etc
soc_title: Woodworking Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Except Sawing
def: Set up, operate, or tend woodworking machines, such as drill presses, lathes, shapers, routers, sanders, planers, and wood nailing machines. May operate computer numerically controlled (CNC) equipment. Workers who primarily program or operate CNC equipment are classified in “Computer Numerically Controlled Tool Operators and Programmers” (51-9160).

title: Woodworkers, all other
def: All woodworkers not listed separately.

title: Plant and system operators
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Power plant operators, distributors, etc
soc_title: Power Plant Operators, Distributors, and Dispatchers
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Nuclear power reactor operators
def: Operate or control nuclear reactors. Move control rods, start and stop equipment, monitor and adjust controls, and record data in logs. Implement emergency procedures when needed. May respond to abnormalities, determine cause, and recommend corrective action.

title: Power distributors and dispatchers
def: Coordinate, regulate, or distribute electricity or steam.

title: Power plant operators
def: Control, operate, or maintain machinery to generate electric power. Includes auxiliary equipment operators. Excludes “Nuclear Power Reactor Operators” (51-8011).

title: Stationary engineers and boiler operators
def: Operate or maintain stationary engines, boilers, or other mechanical equipment to provide utilities for buildings or industrial processes. Operate equipment such as steam engines, generators, motors, turbines, and steam boilers.

title: Water and wastewater treatment plant and system operators
soc_title: Water and Wastewater Treatment Plant and System Operators
def: Operate or control an entire process or system of machines, often through the use of control boards, to transfer or treat water or wastewater.

title: Miscellaneous plant and system operators
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Chemical plant and system operators
def: Control or operate entire chemical processes or system of machines.

title: Gas plant operators
def: Distribute or process gas for utility companies and others by controlling compressors to maintain specified pressures on main pipelines.

title: Petroleum pump system operators, refinery operators, etc
soc_title: Petroleum Pump System Operators, Refinery Operators, and Gaugers
def: Operate or control petroleum refining or processing units. May specialize in controlling manifold and pumping systems, gauging or testing oil in storage tanks, or regulating the flow of oil into pipelines.

title: Plant and system operators, all other
soc_title: Plant and System Operators, All Other
def: All plant and system operators not listed separately.

title: Other production
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Chemical processing machine setters, operators, etc
soc_title: Chemical Processing Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Chemical equipment operators and tenders
def: Operate or tend equipment to control chemical changes or reactions in the processing of industrial or consumer products. Equipment used includes devulcanizers, steam-jacketed kettles, and reactor vessels. Excludes “Chemical Plant and System Operators” (51-8091).

title: Separating, filtering, etc
soc_title: Separating, Filtering, Clarifying, Precipitating, and Still Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
def: Set up, operate, or tend continuous flow or vat-type equipment; filter presses; shaker screens; centrifuges; condenser tubes; precipitating, fermenting, or evaporating tanks; scrubbing towers; or batch stills. These machines extract, sort, or separate liquids, gases, or solids from other materials to recover a refined product. Includes dairy processing equipment operators. Excludes “Chemical Equipment Operators and Tenders” (51-9011).

title: Crushing, grinding, etc
soc_title: Crushing, Grinding, Polishing, Mixing, and Blending Workers
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Crushing, grinding, etc
soc_title: Crushing, Grinding, and Polishing Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
def: Set up, operate, or tend machines to crush, grind, or polish materials, such as coal, glass, grain, stone, food, or rubber.

title: Grinding and polishing workers, hand
def: Grind, sand, or polish, using hand tools or hand-held power tools, a variety of metal, wood, stone, clay, plastic, or glass objects. Includes chippers, buffers, and finishers.

title: Mixing and blending machine setters, operators, etc
soc_title: Mixing and Blending Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
def: Set up, operate, or tend machines to mix or blend materials, such as chemicals, tobacco, liquids, color pigments, or explosive ingredients. Excludes “Food Batchmakers” (51-3092).

title: Cutting workers
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Cutters and trimmers, hand
def: Use hand tools or hand-held power tools to cut and trim a variety of manufactured items, such as carpet, fabric, stone, glass, or rubber.

title: Cutting and slicing machine setters, operators, etc
soc_title: Cutting and Slicing Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
def: Set up, operate, or tend machines that cut or slice materials, such as glass, stone, cork, rubber, tobacco, food, paper, or insulating material. Excludes “Cutting, Punching, and Press Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic” (51-4031), “Textile Cutting Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders” (51-6062), and “Woodworking Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders” (51-7040).

title: Extruding, forming, etc
soc_title: Extruding, Forming, Pressing, and Compacting Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
def: Set up, operate, or tend machines, such as glass-forming machines, plodder machines, and tuber machines, to shape and form products such as glassware, food, rubber, soap, brick, tile, clay, wax, tobacco, or cosmetics. Excludes “Shoe Machine Operators and Tenders” (51-6042) and “Paper Goods Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders” (51-9196).

title: Furnace, kiln, etc
soc_title: Furnace, Kiln, Oven, Drier, and Kettle Operators and Tenders
def: Operate or tend heating equipment other than basic metal, plastic, or food processing equipment. Includes activities such as annealing glass, drying lumber, curing rubber, removing moisture from materials, or boiling soap.

title: Inspectors, testers, etc
soc_title: Inspectors, Testers, Sorters, Samplers, and Weighers
def: Inspect, test, sort, sample, or weigh nonagricultural raw materials or processed, machined, fabricated, or assembled parts or products for defects, wear, and deviations from specifications. May use precision measuring instruments and complex test equipment.

title: Jewelers and precious stone and metal workers
soc_title: Jewelers and Precious Stone and Metal Workers
def: Design, fabricate, adjust, repair, or appraise jewelry, gold, silver, other precious metals, or gems. Includes diamond polishers and gem cutters, and persons who perform precision casting and modeling of molds, casting metal in molds, or setting precious and semiprecious stones for jewelry and related products.

title: Dental and ophthalmic laboratory technicians and medical appliance technicians
soc_title: Dental and Ophthalmic Laboratory Technicians and Medical Appliance Technicians
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Dental laboratory technicians
def: Construct and repair full or partial dentures or dental appliances. Excludes “Dental Assistants” (31-9091).

title: Medical appliance technicians
def: Construct, maintain, or repair medical supportive devices such as braces, orthotics and prosthetic devices, joints, arch supports, and other surgical and medical appliances.

title: Ophthalmic laboratory technicians
def: Cut, grind, and polish eyeglasses, contact lenses, or other precision optical elements. Assemble and mount lenses into frames or process other optical elements. Includes precision lens polishers or grinders, centerer-edgers, and lens mounters. Excludes “Opticians, Dispensing ” (29-2081).

title: Packaging and filling machine operators and tenders
soc_title: Packaging and Filling Machine Operators and Tenders
def: Operate or tend machines to prepare industrial or consumer products for storage or shipment. Includes cannery workers who pack food products.

title: Painting workers
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Painting, coating, etc
def: Paint, coat, or decorate articles, such as furniture, glass, plateware, pottery, jewelry, toys, books, or leather. Excludes “Artists and Related Workers" (27-1010), “Designers” (27-1020), “Photographic Process Workers and Processing Machine Operators” (51-9151), and “Etchers and Engravers” (51-9194).

title: Coating, painting, etc
soc_title: Coating, Painting, and Spraying Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
def: Set up, operate, or tend spraying or rolling machines to coat or paint any of a wide variety of products, including glassware, cloth, ceramics, metal, plastic, paper, or wood, with lacquer, silver, copper, rubber, varnish, glaze, enamel, oil, or rust-proofing materials. Includes painters of transportation vehicles such as painters in auto body repair facilities. Excludes “Plating Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic” (51-4193).

title: Semiconductor processing technicians
def: Perform any or all of the following functions in the manufacture of electronic semiconductors: load semiconductor material into furnace; saw formed ingots into segments; load individual segment into crystal growing chamber and monitor controls; locate crystal axis in ingot using x-ray equipment and saw ingots into wafers; and clean, polish, and load wafers into series of special purpose furnaces, chemical baths, and equipment used to form circuitry and change conductive properties.

title: Photographic process workers and processing machine operators
soc_title: Photographic Process Workers and Processing Machine Operators
def: Perform work involved in developing and processing photographic images from film or digital media. May perform precision tasks such as editing photographic negatives and prints.

title: Computer numerically controlled tool operators and programmers
soc_title: Computer Numerically Controlled Tool Operators and Programmers
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Computer numerically controlled tool operators
def: Operate computer-controlled tools, machines, or robots to machine or process parts, tools, or other work pieces made of metal, plastic, wood, stone, or other materials. May also set up and maintain equipment.

title: Computer numerically controlled tool programmers
def: Develop programs to control machining or processing of materials by automatic machine tools, equipment, or systems. May also set up, operate, or maintain equipment.

title: Miscellaneous production workers
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Adhesive bonding machine operators and tenders
soc_title: Adhesive Bonding Machine Operators and Tenders
def: Operate or tend bonding machines that use adhesives to join items for further processing or to form a completed product. Processes include joining veneer sheets into plywood; gluing paper; or joining rubber and rubberized fabric parts, plastic, simulated leather, or other materials. Excludes “Shoe Machine Operators and Tenders” (51-6042).

title: Cleaning, washing, etc
soc_title: Cleaning, Washing, and Metal Pickling Equipment Operators and Tenders
def: Operate or tend machines to wash or clean products, such as barrels or kegs, glass items, tin plate, food, pulp, coal, plastic, or rubber, to remove impurities.

title: Cooling and freezing equipment operators and tenders
soc_title: Cooling and Freezing Equipment Operators and Tenders
def: Operate or tend equipment such as cooling and freezing units, refrigerators, batch freezers, and freezing tunnels, to cool or freeze products, food, blood plasma, and chemicals.

title: Etchers and engravers
def: Engrave or etch metal, wood, rubber, or other materials. Includes such workers as etcher-circuit processors, pantograph engravers, and silk screen etchers. Photoengravers are included in “Prepress Technicians and Workers” (51-5111).

title: Molders, shapers, etc
soc_title: Molders, Shapers, and Casters, Except Metal and Plastic
def: Mold, shape, form, cast, or carve products such as food products, figurines, tile, pipes, and candles consisting of clay, glass, plaster, concrete, stone, or combinations of materials.

title: Paper goods machine setters, operators, etc
soc_title: Paper Goods Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
def: Set up, operate, or tend paper goods machines that perform a variety of functions, such as converting, sawing, corrugating, banding, wrapping, boxing, stitching, forming, or sealing paper or paperboard sheets into products.

title: Tire builders
def: Operate machines to build tires.

title: Helpers--production workers
def: Help production workers by performing duties requiring less skill. Duties include supplying or holding materials or tools, and cleaning work area and equipment. Apprentice workers are classified in the appropriate production occupations (51-0000).

title: Production workers, all other
def: All production workers not listed separately. Excludes “Packers and Packagers, Hand” (53-7064).

title: Transportation and material moving
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Supervisors of transportation and material moving workers
soc_title: Supervisors of Transportation and Material Moving Workers
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Aircraft cargo handling supervisors
def: Supervise and coordinate the activities of ground crew in the loading, unloading, securing, and staging of aircraft cargo or baggage. May determine the quantity and orientation of cargo and compute aircraft center of gravity. May accompany aircraft as member of flight crew and monitor and handle cargo in flight, and assist and brief passengers on safety and emergency procedures. Includes loadmasters.

title: First-line supervisors of transportation and material moving workers, except aircraft cargo handling supervisors
def: No job definition found.

title: Air transportation workers
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Aircraft pilots and flight engineers
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Airline pilots, copilots, etc
soc_title: Airline Pilots, Copilots, and Flight Engineers
def: Pilot and navigate the flight of fixed-wing aircraft, usually on scheduled air carrier routes, for the transport of passengers and cargo. Requires Federal Air Transport certificate and rating for specific aircraft type used. Includes regional, national, and international airline pilots and flight instructors of airline pilots. Excludes “Electro-Mechanical and Mechatronics Technologists and Technicians” (17-3024).

title: Commercial pilots
def: Pilot and navigate the flight of fixed-wing aircraft on nonscheduled air carrier routes, or helicopters. Requires Commercial Pilot certificate. Includes charter pilots with similar certification, and air ambulance and air tour pilots. Excludes regional, national, and international airline pilots. Excludes “Electro-Mechanical and Mechatronics Technologists and Technicians” (17-3024).

title: Air traffic controllers and airfield operations specialists
soc_title: Air Traffic Controllers and Airfield Operations Specialists
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Air traffic controllers
def: Control air traffic on and within vicinity of airport, and movement of air traffic between altitude sectors and control centers, according to established procedures and policies. Authorize, regulate, and control commercial airline flights according to government or company regulations to expedite and ensure flight safety.

title: Airfield operations specialists
def: Ensure the safe takeoff and landing of commercial and military aircraft. Duties include coordination between air-traffic control and maintenance personnel, dispatching, using airfield landing and navigational aids, implementing airfield safety procedures, monitoring and maintaining flight records, and applying knowledge of weather information.

title: Flight attendants
def: Monitor safety of the aircraft cabin. Provide services to airline passengers, explain safety information, serve food and beverages, and respond to emergency incidents.

title: Motor vehicle operators
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Ambulance drivers and attendants, except emergency medical technicians
soc_title: Ambulance Drivers and Attendants, Except Emergency Medical Technicians
def: Drive ambulance or assist ambulance driver in transporting sick, injured, or convalescent persons. Assist in lifting patients.

title: Driver/sales workers and truck drivers
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Driver/sales workers
def: Drive truck or other vehicle over established routes or within an established territory and sell or deliver goods, such as food products, including restaurant take-out items, or pick up or deliver items such as commercial laundry. May also take orders, collect payment, or stock merchandise at point of delivery. Excludes “Coin, Vending, and Amusement Machine Servicers and Repairers” (49-9091) and “Light Truck Drivers” (53-3033).

title: Heavy and tractor-trailer truck drivers
def: Drive a tractor-trailer combination or a truck with a capacity of at least 26,001 pounds Gross Vehicle Weight (GVW). May be required to unload truck. Requires commercial drivers’ license. Includes tow truck drivers. Excludes “Refuse and Recyclable Material Collectors” (53-7081).

title: Light truck drivers
def: Drive a light vehicle, such as a truck or van, with a capacity of less than 26,001 pounds Gross Vehicle Weight (GVW), primarily to pick up merchandise or packages from a distribution center and deliver. May load and unload vehicle. Excludes “Couriers and Messengers” (43-5021) and “Driver/Sales Workers” (53-3031).

title: Passenger vehicle drivers
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Bus drivers, school
def: Drive a school bus to transport students. Ensure adherence to safety rules. May assist students in boarding or exiting.

title: Bus drivers, transit and intercity
def: Drive bus or motor coach, including regular route operations, charters, and private carriage. May assist passengers with baggage. May collect fares or tickets.

title: Shuttle drivers and chauffeurs
def: Drive a motor vehicle to transport passengers on a planned or scheduled basis. May collect a fare. Includes nonemergency medical transporters and hearse drivers. Excludes “Ambulance Drivers and Attendants, Except Emergency Medical Technicians” (53-3011) and “Taxi Drivers” (53-3054).

title: Taxi drivers
def: Drive a motor vehicle to transport passengers on an unplanned basis and charge a fare, usually based on a meter. Excludes “Shuttle Drivers and Chauffeurs” (53-3053).

title: Motor vehicle operators, all other
def: All motor vehicle operators not listed separately.

title: Rail transportation workers
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Locomotive engineers and operators
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Locomotive engineers
def: Drive electric, diesel-electric, steam, or gas-turbine-electric locomotives to transport passengers or freight. Interpret train orders, electronic or manual signals, and railroad rules and regulations. Excludes “Engineers” (17-2011 through 17-2199).

title: Rail yard engineers, dinkey operators, etc
soc_title: Rail Yard Engineers, Dinkey Operators, and Hostlers
def: Drive switching or other locomotive or dinkey engines within railroad yard, industrial plant, quarry, construction project, or similar location.

title: Railroad brake, signal, etc
soc_title: Railroad Brake, Signal, and Switch Operators and Locomotive Firers
def: Operate or monitor railroad track switches or locomotive instruments. May couple or uncouple rolling stock to make up or break up trains. Watch for and relay traffic signals. May inspect couplings, air hoses, journal boxes, and hand brakes. May watch for dragging equipment or obstacles on rights-of-way.

title: Railroad conductors and yardmasters
def: Coordinate activities of switch-engine crew within railroad yard, industrial plant, or similar location. Conductors coordinate activities of train crew on passenger or freight trains. Yardmasters review train schedules and switching orders and coordinate activities of workers engaged in railroad traffic operations, such as the makeup or breakup of trains and yard switching.

title: Subway and streetcar operators
def: Operate subway or elevated suburban trains with no separate locomotive, or electric-powered streetcar, to transport passengers. May handle fares.

title: Rail transportation workers, all other
def: All rail transportation workers not listed separately.

title: Water transportation workers
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Sailors and marine oilers
def: Stand watch to look for obstructions in path of vessel, measure water depth, turn wheel on bridge, or use emergency equipment as directed by captain, mate, or pilot. Break out, rig, overhaul, and store cargo-handling gear, stationary rigging, and running gear. Perform a variety of maintenance tasks to preserve the painted surface of the ship and to maintain line and ship equipment. Must hold government-issued certification and tankerman certification when working aboard liquid-carrying vessels. Includes able seamen and ordinary seamen.

title: Ship and boat captains and operators
soc_title: Ship and Boat Captains and Operators
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Captains, mates, etc
soc_title: Captains, Mates, and Pilots of Water Vessels
def: Command or supervise operations of ships and water vessels, such as tugboats and ferryboats. Required to hold license issued by U.S. Coast Guard. Excludes “Motorboat Operators” (53-5022).

title: Motorboat operators
def: Operate small motor-driven boats. May assist in navigational activities.

title: Ship engineers
def: Supervise and coordinate activities of crew engaged in operating and maintaining engines, boilers, deck machinery, and electrical, sanitary, and refrigeration equipment aboard ship. Excludes “Engineers” (17-2000).

title: Other transportation workers
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Bridge and lock tenders
def: Operate and tend bridges, canal locks, and lighthouses to permit marine passage on inland waterways, near shores, and at danger points in waterway passages. May supervise such operations. Includes drawbridge operators, lock operators, and slip bridge operators.

title: Parking attendants
def: Park vehicles or issue tickets for customers in a parking lot or garage. May park or tend vehicles in environments such as a car dealership or rental car facility. May collect fee.

title: Transportation service attendants
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Automotive and watercraft service attendants
def: Service automobiles, buses, trucks, boats, and other automotive or marine vehicles with fuel, lubricants, and accessories. Collect payment for services and supplies. May lubricate vehicle, change motor oil, refill antifreeze, or replace lights or other accessories, such as windshield wiper blades or fan belts. May repair or replace tires. Excludes “Cashiers” (41-2011).

title: Aircraft service attendants
def: Service aircraft with fuel. May de-ice aircraft, refill water and cooling agents, empty sewage tanks, service air and oxygen systems, or clean and polish exterior.

title: Traffic technicians
def: Conduct field studies to determine traffic volume, speed, effectiveness of signals, adequacy of lighting, and other factors influencing traffic conditions, under direction of traffic engineer.

title: Transportation inspectors
def: Inspect equipment or goods in connection with the safe transport of cargo or people. Includes rail transportation inspectors, such as freight inspectors, rail inspectors, and other inspectors of transportation vehicles not elsewhere classified. Excludes “Transportation Security Screeners” (33-9093).

title: Passenger attendants
def: Provide services to ensure the safety of passengers aboard ships, buses, trains, or within the station or terminal. Perform duties such as explaining the use of safety equipment, serving meals or beverages, or answering questions related to travel. Excludes “Baggage Porters and Bellhops” (39-6011) and “Flight Attendants” (53-2031).

title: Transportation workers, all other
def: All transportation workers not listed separately.

title: Material moving workers
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Conveyor operators and tenders
def: Control or tend conveyors or conveyor systems that move materials or products to and from stockpiles, processing stations, departments, or vehicles. May control speed and routing of materials or products.

title: Crane and tower operators
def: Operate mechanical boom and cable or tower and cable equipment to lift and move materials, machines, or products in many directions.

title: Dredge operators
def: Operate dredge to remove sand, gravel, or other materials in order to excavate and maintain navigable channels in waterways.

title: Hoist and winch operators
def: Operate or tend hoists or winches to lift and pull loads using power-operated cable equipment. Excludes “Crane and Tower Operators” (53-7021).

title: Industrial truck and tractor operators
def: Operate industrial trucks or tractors equipped to move materials around a warehouse, storage yard, factory, construction site, or similar location. Excludes “Logging Equipment Operators” (45-4022).

title: Laborers and material movers
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Cleaners of vehicles and equipment
def: Wash or otherwise clean vehicles, machinery, and other equipment. Use such materials as water, cleaning agents, brushes, cloths, and hoses. Excludes “Janitors and Cleaners, Except Maids and Housekeeping Cleaners” (37-2011).

title: Laborers and freight, stock, etc
soc_title: Laborers and Freight, Stock, and Material Movers, Hand
def: Manually move freight, stock, luggage, or other materials, or perform other general labor. Includes all manual laborers not elsewhere classified. Excludes “Construction Laborers” (47-2061) and “Helpers, Construction Trades” (47-3011 through 47-3019). Excludes “Material Moving Workers” (53-7011 through 53-7199) who use power equipment.

title: Machine feeders and offbearers
def: Feed materials into or remove materials from machines or equipment that is automatic or tended by other workers.

title: Packers and packagers, hand
def: Pack or package by hand a wide variety of products and materials.

title: Stockers and order fillers
def: Receive, store, and issue merchandise, materials, equipment, and other items from stockroom, warehouse, or storage yard to fill shelves, racks, tables, or customers’ orders. May operate power equipment to fill orders. May mark prices on merchandise and set up sales displays. Excludes “Shipping, Receiving, and Inventory Clerks” (43-5071), “Laborers and Freight, Stock, and Material Movers, Hand” (53-7062), and “Packers and Packagers, Hand” (53-7064).

title: Pumping station operators
def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

title: Gas compressor and gas pumping station operators
soc_title: Gas Compressor and Gas Pumping Station Operators
def: Operate steam-, gas-, electric motor-, or internal combustion-engine driven compressors. Transmit, compress, or recover gases, such as butane, nitrogen, hydrogen, and natural gas.

title: Pump operators, except wellhead pumpers
def: Tend, control, or operate power-driven, stationary, or portable pumps and manifold systems to transfer gases, oil, other liquids, slurries, or powdered materials to and from various vessels and processes.

title: Wellhead pumpers
def: Operate power pumps and auxiliary equipment to produce flow of oil or gas from wells in oil field.

title: Refuse and recyclable material collectors
def: Collect and dump refuse or recyclable materials from containers into truck. May drive truck.

title: Tank car, truck, etc
soc_title: Tank Car, Truck, and Ship Loaders
def: Load and unload chemicals and bulk solids, such as coal, sand, and grain, into or from tank cars, trucks, or ships, using material moving equipment. May perform a variety of other tasks relating to shipment of products. May gauge or sample shipping tanks and test them for leaks.

title: Material moving workers, all other
def: All material moving workers not listed separately.
